#What are templates?
#Templates are files that contain static data as well as placeholders for dynamic data. They are used to generate HTML dynamically by replacing the placeholders with actual data at runtime. In web development, templates help separate the presentation layer from the business logic, making it easier to manage and maintain code.

#Django templates contain static data (HTML, CSS, JavaScript) and placeholders for dynamic data. The placeholders are defined using template tags and variables, which are replaced with actual data when the template is rendered. This allows developers to create dynamic web pages that can display different content based on user input or other factors.
#they are downloaded from the internet and are used to create dynamic web pages. They are often used in web frameworks like Django, Flask, and Jinja2 to generate HTML content based on data from a database or user input.
#they help developers create dynamic web pages by allowing them to define placeholders for data that will be filled in at runtime. This makes it easier to manage and maintain code, as the presentation layer is separated from the business logic.

